### Полный пайплайн компилятора (Архитектурный граф)

toc
↓ Source Code - raw text string
↓ Lexer - stream of tokens (keywords, symbols)
↓ Parser (CST) - concrete syntax tree (keeps exact formatting & punctuation)
↓ Surface AST - logical tree structure (classes, loops, syntax sugar)
↓ Desugar & Resolve - remove syntax sugar (e.g., for to while), bind string names to unique IDs
↓ HIR (Semantic AST) - high-level graph of references via unique Symbol IDs (powers IDEs/LSP)
↓ Type Checker & Normalizer - validate semantics, prove type safety, pre-calculate static values
↓ Core AST - pure mathematical model (Calculus of Constructions: Lambdas, Records, no classes/interfaces)
↓ Optimizer (Low-level IR / SSA) - hardware-agnostic optimizations (Static Single Assignment, dead code removal)
↓ Code Generator - translate to target CPU instructions (x86, ARM) or bytecode (WASM, JVM)
↓ Binary Code - final executable (0s and 1s)

detailed
1 text (source code)
2 tokens (lexer: splitting text into words and symbols)
3 AST (parser: tree construction, declarations, statements)
4 scopes & symbols (name table: registering defined types and variables)
5 types (type checker: checking predefined types, outputting calculated types)
6 static values (optimizer: calculating constants before runtime)
7 dynamic values (code generation/runtime: things that are calculated only when the program runs)
